#. type: Title ====
#, no-wrap
msgid "Protecting a Stateless Service Using a Bearer Token"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If the adapter is configured with the `bearer-only` configuration option, the policy enforcer decides whether a request\n"
"to access a protected resource is allowed or denied based on the permissions of the bearer token.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"HTTP GET example passing an RPT as a bearer token\n"
"```bash\n"
"GET /my-resource-server/my-protected-resource HTTP/1.1\n"
"Host: host.com\n"
"Authorization: Bearer ${RPT}\n"
"...\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "In this example, a *keycloak.json* file in your application is similar to the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example of WEB-INF/keycloak.json with the bearer-only configuration option"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```json\n"
"...\n"
"\"bearer-only\" : true,\n"
"...\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid "Authorization Services Guide"
msgid "Authorization Response"
msgstr "Authorization Servicesガイド"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When a client tries to access a resource server with a bearer token that is lacking permissions to access a protected resource, the resource server\n"
"responds with a *401* status code and a `WWW-Authenticate` header. The value of the `WWW-Authenticate` header depends on the authorization protocol\n"
"in use by the resource server.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "Here is an example of a response from a resource server that is using UMA as the authorization protocol:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```bash\n"
"HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized\n"
"WWW-Authenticate: UMA realm=\"photoz-restful-api\",as_uri=\"http://localhost:8080/auth/realms/photoz/authz/authorize\",ticket=\"${PERMISSION_TICKET}\"\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "And another example when the resource server is using the Entitlement protocol:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```bash\n"
"HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized\n"
"WWW-Authenticate: KC_ETT realm=\"photoz-restful-api\",as_uri=\"http://localhost:8080/auth/realms/photoz/authz/entitlement\"\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once  a client receives a response from the server, it examines the status code and `WWW-Authenticate` header to obtain an RPT from the {project_name} Server.\n"
msgstr ""
